14
00:00:00,950 --> 00:00:02,970
Previously on Salem.

15
00:00:02,970 --> 00:00:04,740
Witch！

16
00:00:04,750 --> 00:00:07,750
No woman in Salem has ever had that kind of power.

17
00:00:07,750 --> 00:00:09,650
Not even Mary Sibley.

18
00:00:09,650 --> 00:00:11,540
The lady of the house is mine.

19
00:00:11,890 --> 00:00:13,690
We've uncovered a witch.

20
00:00:14,130 --> 00:00:16,890
How long may we enjoy your curative presence in town?

21
00:00:17,310 --> 00:00:23,080
Until every last devil's whore of a witch in Salem is dead.

22
00:00:23,080 --> 00:00:24,890
Petrus' physic will last but a day,

23
00:00:24,890 --> 00:00:27,610
And then Mr. Sibley will awake, lucid and eager.

24
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:29,780
To tell Increase everything.

25
00:00:53,990 --> 00:00:54,890
Choose one.

26
00:00:59,590 --> 00:01:00,370
Drink.

27
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,960
Drink and...enjoy.

28
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:07,650
Only mere mortals are vulnerable to manmade spirits.

29
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:10,400
As a man, you are an abomination,

30
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:12,600
but you are no witch.

31
00:01:13,980 --> 00:01:18,530
Now begone with you and your...pitiful weakness.

32
00:01:26,060 --> 00:01:28,680
Time to wake, my good madam.

33
00:01:55,840 --> 00:02:00,130
Let them no more say, "God must do all,"

34
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:02,660
and so encourage themselves

35
00:02:03,550 --> 00:02:07,350
to live in a careless neglect of god 

36
00:02:07,350 --> 00:02:09,740
and of their own souls

37
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,830
and salvation!

38
00:02:12,290 --> 00:02:14,290
The devil has made 

39
00:02:14,290 --> 00:02:18,630
a dreadful knot of witches in the country,

40
00:02:19,060 --> 00:02:21,330
and, by the help of witches,

41
00:02:21,330 --> 00:02:25,270
has dreadfully increased that knot.

42
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:35,650
Oh, children, children, be afraid

43
00:02:36,450 --> 00:02:39,910
and go not prayerless to your bed

44
00:02:41,290 --> 00:02:44,070
lest the devil be your bedfellow.

45
00:03:28,930 --> 00:03:31,940
*Pound me the witch drums*

46
00:03:31,940 --> 00:03:33,120
*Witch drums*

47
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:36,610
*Pound me the witch drums*

48
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:39,860
*Pound me the witch drums*

49
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:41,150
*The witch drums*

50
00:03:41,150 --> 00:03:43,630
*Better pray for hell*

51
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:49,620
*Not hallelujah*

52
00:04:20,080 --> 00:04:21,300
Good morning, reverend.

53
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,300
Mrs. Sibley.

54
00:04:27,410 --> 00:04:28,160
Join me?

55
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:35,990
There are no words

56
00:04:35,990 --> 00:04:38,520
to encompass my overwhelming gratitude

57
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,470
at your reclamation of my husband.

58
00:04:40,470 --> 00:04:42,070
When I think what might have transpired

59
00:04:42,070 --> 00:04:43,590
- had you not been there... - Indeed?

60
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:46,020
Exactly what might have transpired?

61
00:04:46,510 --> 00:04:47,580
- Excuse me? - well...

62
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:52,240
Would not your slave girl simply have taken him on to hospital?

63
00:04:52,490 --> 00:04:52,990
Yes.

64
00:04:52,990 --> 00:04:56,350
Yes, it was you who sent her to his rescue,

65
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:57,290
was it not?

66
00:04:57,290 --> 00:04:58,690
Once I'd heard of the accident.

67
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,930
I am perplexed, though.

68
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:08,730
Tell me, why was George scurried off with such haste and secrecy?

69
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,180
He goes often to Boston.

70
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:14,440
- His illness. - He's not ill.

71
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:16,170
- He's spelled. - No.

72
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:18,700
That's impossible.

73
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:19,630
Consider...

74
00:05:20,030 --> 00:05:24,430
has not George suffered this mysterious malady

75
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:27,880
without explication for several years now,

76
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:31,180
and have not the doctors expressed utter befuddlement

77
00:05:31,180 --> 00:05:32,700
as to its cause?

78
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:35,580
- Yes, but... - Yes. In such cases,

79
00:05:35,580 --> 00:05:37,620
The answer is oft the simplest one.

80
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:39,270
George is not ill.

81
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:42,950
He is under the influence of the devil's darkest tool --

82
00:05:43,410 --> 00:05:44,620
a witch's spell.

83
00:05:45,260 --> 00:05:49,670
And it is quite likely that this speller resides close at hearth.

84
00:05:50,610 --> 00:05:51,530
No.

85
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:56,000
Perhaps even in the hallowed halls of your own home.

86
00:05:59,510 --> 00:06:00,660
Say it.

87
00:06:01,090 --> 00:06:02,010
Say what?

88
00:06:02,060 --> 00:06:03,450
The accusation.

89
00:06:04,590 --> 00:06:06,120
It dances on your tongue.

90
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:08,780
Well, I assure you, you are mistaken.

91
00:06:15,490 --> 00:06:18,140
Then I wish to bring my husband home immediately.

92
00:06:18,140 --> 00:06:19,830
I think not, Mrs. Sibley.

93
00:06:19,830 --> 00:06:20,950
You would deny me that right?

94
00:06:20,950 --> 00:06:22,510
I must deny you that right

95
00:06:22,510 --> 00:06:25,660
until we can discover the origin of the spell.

96
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:34,080
Then I would ask, or, rather, insist,

97
00:06:34,340 --> 00:06:36,410
that someone attend to Mr. Sibley.

98
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:39,480
Someone who has experience with his travails.

99
00:06:40,130 --> 00:06:41,340
What about that young man...

100
00:06:41,340 --> 00:06:43,850
the one who was to take him to Boston, huh?

101
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:45,880
- Isaac? - Ah.

102
00:06:47,780 --> 00:06:48,810
Isaac will do.

103
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:54,290
He sleeps still?

104
00:06:55,660 --> 00:06:57,190
Under the care of sentries.

105
00:06:58,350 --> 00:06:59,160
Oh, and, Mary.

106
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,420
Be of good heart.

107
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:05,200
Mr. Lamb, the barkeep, tells me that he may wake at any moment.

108
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:13,180
Cotton.

109
00:07:14,660 --> 00:07:15,370
Cotton.

110
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,830
No difference between me and those that already rest.

111
00:07:24,380 --> 00:07:25,900
Besides a still-beating heart

112
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:28,640
in a shell where my soul no longer resides.

113
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:30,610
Oh, boy.

114
00:07:39,770 --> 00:07:40,870
Good morning, reverend.

115
00:07:42,810 --> 00:07:43,710
I wonder --

116
00:07:44,590 --> 00:07:46,610
what would it take to get you to your feet?

117
00:07:47,740 --> 00:07:49,170
Why would you wish to?

118
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:57,670
I fear I may have...

119
00:07:58,620 --> 00:08:01,160
judged you too harshly, Reverend Mather.

120
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:05,150
It is only now, when leaving my childhood behind,

121
00:08:05,690 --> 00:08:08,170
that I realize we are, past and forever,

122
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,960
our fathers' children.

123
00:08:10,580 --> 00:08:12,940
And we can no more control who they be

124
00:08:12,940 --> 00:08:14,540
and how they came to form us

125
00:08:15,060 --> 00:08:17,320
then we can the rise and setting of the sun.

126
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,410
I am sorry about your girl.

127
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:24,650
Thank you.

128
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,020
May we see you home?

129
00:08:37,230 --> 00:08:37,960
Come on.

130
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,850
Once he's settled, Captain,

131
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:52,000
may I ask a favor of you?

132
00:08:52,890 --> 00:08:53,740
Surely.

133
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:56,460
"I think not, Mrs. Sibley."

134
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:59,910
As if he were Socrates and I, a student at his knee.

135
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:01,310
Let me kill him, please.

136
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,010
No.

137
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,600
Let me ease this burden for you, as I've done the others.

138
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:06,420
Increase Mather is known throughout the world,

139
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:08,100
new and old.

140
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:10,030
His disappearance or death will not be taken lightly.

141
00:09:10,030 --> 00:09:12,260
His head will sit on no man's platter.

142
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,840
He's no match for you, certainly.

143
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:15,830
That is where you are wrong, child.

144
00:09:16,110 --> 00:09:17,690
This is our truest test

145
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:19,010
to battle equals.

146
00:09:20,950 --> 00:09:22,100
Mrs. Sibley.

147
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:23,010
Reverend.

148
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:24,620
Mercy.

149
00:09:25,370 --> 00:09:26,060
Hello.

150
00:09:26,130 --> 00:09:28,430
I wonder if I might have a private word

151
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,650
with my daughter.

152
00:09:29,650 --> 00:09:31,390
I think not, Reverend.

153
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,950
- I - Fetch me Isaac.

154
00:09:35,070 --> 00:09:35,820
Now.

155
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:39,760
I am, um...

156
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:44,980
astounded at the charity you've shown my child,

157
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:47,870
but if I wish to see her, 

158
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,260
is that not a father's right?

159
00:09:50,260 --> 00:09:52,740
Why, in particular, do you wish to see her, Reverend?

160
00:09:53,770 --> 00:09:56,800
Were you perhaps considering another exorcism?

161
00:09:57,370 --> 00:09:58,520
Do your days grow dull,

162
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:00,800
lacking a child to beat and torture

163
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,590
and the nights far too lonely with no daughter to visit?

164
00:10:03,590 --> 00:10:05,700
- I would never - Mercy is mine.

165
00:10:06,370 --> 00:10:09,510
Return here again and these accusations will be made public.

166
00:10:23,210 --> 00:10:25,300
What of master Sibley? Has he woken?

167
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:28,750
The elders will wait no longer.

168
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:30,870
They require an audience with you today.

169
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:53,470
Has he woken?

170
00:10:58,810 --> 00:11:00,240
Any moment now.

171
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:14,650
It were an accident, ma'am.

172
00:11:14,650 --> 00:11:15,840
A wayward timber in the path,

173
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,920
and we found ourselves at sixes and sevens.

174
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:19,240
It's okay, Isaac.

175
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,660
I know you've done your best.

176
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:22,780
The reverend summons me now,

177
00:11:22,780 --> 00:11:24,940
heaven knows why, but I fear each second he's made to wait --

178
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:27,350
He will ask you to watch over Mr. Sibley.

179
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:31,650
- He will? - At my grave insistence,

180
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:33,380
since he refuses my desire

181
00:11:33,380 --> 00:11:35,330
to bring my husband home to proper care.

182
00:11:36,010 --> 00:11:37,760
He refuses you?

183
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:40,800
Salem reels out of control like an unwieldy spin top

184
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,390
at the whim of Increase Mather.

185
00:11:44,230 --> 00:11:46,950
A tonic... the pain and ease of sleep.

186
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,870
Isaac, I beseech you,

187
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,480
in this most private and important matter,

188
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,970
do my bidding where I cannot.

189
00:11:51,970 --> 00:11:53,020
Oh, uh...

190
00:11:53,530 --> 00:11:55,870
Dose him immediately and keep him so.

191
00:11:56,810 --> 00:11:58,260
George should not be made to suffer

192
00:11:58,260 --> 00:12:00,650
for Mather senior's unfounded suspicions.

193
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:04,630
H-he shall not.

194
00:12:09,230 --> 00:12:10,050
And Isaac...

195
00:12:13,410 --> 00:12:14,450
Between us.

196
00:12:15,620 --> 00:12:17,560
Like so many of Salem's secrets.

197
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,310
Between us.

198
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,250
Are you aware, son?

199
00:12:27,110 --> 00:12:30,520
Your story is known far and wide throughout the land.

200
00:12:31,430 --> 00:12:34,200
Isaac the fornicator.

201
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:37,710
No, no, no. Do not bow your head in shame.

202
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,010
Head up. Get your head up.

203
00:12:40,010 --> 00:12:41,410
Head up. Head up.

204
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:46,530
The story of Isaac the fornicator

205
00:12:48,070 --> 00:12:49,170
is a holy one.

206
00:12:49,430 --> 00:12:53,300
It is used as a living precedent by we puritans

207
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:58,150
to illustrate to the children the evils of lust.

208
00:12:58,150 --> 00:13:00,580
No, no. Your sin and your suffering...

209
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:05,550
It has been transformed into a great and a holy blessing.

210
00:13:06,660 --> 00:13:07,660
For, my son...

211
00:13:10,310 --> 00:13:11,980
You felt the hand of God.

212
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:17,910
He's touched you.

213
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:20,870
He's working through you.

214
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:23,050
He's chosen you.

215
00:13:23,330 --> 00:13:24,600
No.

216
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:28,740
How many can say that they have been chosen by God?

217
00:13:29,980 --> 00:13:31,910
Chosen for what?

218
00:13:33,050 --> 00:13:38,610
Son, have you ever imagined a world beyond Salem?

219
00:13:39,710 --> 00:13:41,340
- I... - Get your head up, your head up,

220
00:13:41,340 --> 00:13:42,910
Your head up, your head up.

221
00:13:44,620 --> 00:13:46,410
I have a good life here, sir.

222
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:50,660
Yes, performing meager errands for Mrs. Sibley.

223
00:13:50,660 --> 00:13:53,540
She's been good to me. Always.

224
00:13:53,540 --> 00:13:56,090
Her charity binds you to her bidding.

225
00:13:56,450 --> 00:13:59,000
No. No, no, no, Isaac.

226
00:14:00,570 --> 00:14:01,620
Out there.

227
00:14:03,690 --> 00:14:05,140
Out there, boy!

228
00:14:08,270 --> 00:14:09,410
There's a vast world out there,

229
00:14:09,410 --> 00:14:12,500
full of... full of opportunities,

230
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:16,560
and if you... if you would walk the straight road

231
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:18,450
in the sunlight with your head up,

232
00:14:20,210 --> 00:14:22,180
I would take you with me to see it.

233
00:14:22,190 --> 00:14:23,030
I would.

234
00:14:24,090 --> 00:14:25,060
Would you like that?

235
00:14:25,370 --> 00:14:27,120
What would I have to do?

236
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:27,820
Well...

237
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:31,290
You will have to --

238
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:34,490
Have to tend to Mr. Sibley there.

239
00:14:34,490 --> 00:14:35,290
You'll have to...

240
00:14:36,340 --> 00:14:38,980
...make certain that he is fresh and tidy,

241
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:42,450
and that is no easy task, hmm?

242
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:48,510
Most importantly, you must alert me the moment that he wakes.

243
00:14:50,060 --> 00:14:50,880
Yes.

244
00:14:56,670 --> 00:14:58,620
Can you do that, hmm?

245
00:15:00,610 --> 00:15:02,290
Do you mind me asking, sir,

246
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:04,950
What these are for?

247
00:15:06,060 --> 00:15:10,130
Protection for Mr. Sibley against...

248
00:15:11,710 --> 00:15:13,500
outer forces.

249
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:16,930
It's cremated ash...

250
00:15:17,420 --> 00:15:19,610
...of a 200-year-old witch.

251
00:15:20,990 --> 00:15:22,320
And, Isaac...

252
00:15:25,390 --> 00:15:27,100
I burned her myself.

253
00:15:30,580 --> 00:15:34,260
So, the roof needs patching there and there,

254
00:15:34,260 --> 00:15:36,280
A fresh coat of paint wouldn't hurt,

255
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:38,640
nor would four or five more beds for the smaller children,

256
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:41,450
And... I'm overwhelming you.

257
00:15:41,450 --> 00:15:42,340
No, no.

258
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:45,010
I'm eager to put my energies to good.

259
00:15:45,010 --> 00:15:45,980
Exactly.

260
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:54,580
The children are frightened, captain.

261
00:15:55,930 --> 00:15:58,530
Another hung today and not an inkling who's to be next.

262
00:16:00,170 --> 00:16:01,990
They're unsure who to fear more...

263
00:16:02,650 --> 00:16:05,240
Witches or those who pursue them.

264
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:06,930
Well, who can blame them?

265
00:16:10,030 --> 00:16:11,540
He doesn't play with the others.

266
00:16:12,490 --> 00:16:13,650
The dark-haired boy.

267
00:16:15,710 --> 00:16:17,270
He's been here two years.

268
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:20,520
His parents were murdered by Indians.

269
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:21,790
They say he saw.

270
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:25,260
No one knows how he survived.

271
00:16:25,990 --> 00:16:27,140
Has anyone asked?

272
00:16:28,980 --> 00:16:30,410
He doesn't talk.

273
00:16:31,530 --> 00:16:33,820
At least, not anymore.

274
00:16:34,630 --> 00:16:37,080
Not since...then.

275
00:16:45,310 --> 00:16:46,290
Excuse me.

276
00:16:49,090 --> 00:16:51,200
Do you know anything about patching a roof?

277
00:16:58,900 --> 00:16:59,870
Mrs. Sibley?

278
00:17:00,860 --> 00:17:02,000
The mistress is out.

279
00:17:04,610 --> 00:17:07,400
Anything needed to be said to her can be said to me.

280
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:15,930
Oh, that's beautiful!

281
00:17:18,490 --> 00:17:19,640
My familiar.

282
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:25,060
Familiar?

283
00:17:25,070 --> 00:17:28,400
A gift from the devil to do my bidding,

284
00:17:29,410 --> 00:17:31,090
My spiritual companion.

285
00:17:35,860 --> 00:17:37,300
This is how she feeds.

286
00:17:48,210 --> 00:17:49,520
Will I get a familiar?

287
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:51,620
In time.

288
00:17:53,380 --> 00:17:54,640
How do I choose?

289
00:17:54,890 --> 00:17:55,890
You don't.

